@WisEngineer 

You should do a little research. MACAROONS and macarons are different things, but there are almond MACAROONS out there, too. 

MACAROONS are favorite desserts of Jewish families at Passover, when flour products other than matzo are forbidden. Coconut and almond MACAROONS are among the most popular types.

@WisEngineer 

Well, I do believe you are correct. That grabbed my attention too. Macarons are the ones made with almond flour. I'm not a huge fan but my coconut MACAROONs are legendary... especially where my family resides, right in your neck of the woods. I'm basically barred from attending family gatherings without them. 

I do use flour in them but regular flour... and I add crushed almonds and dip their bottoms in chocolate.

@Steve L 

Okay, I see, so I was thinking that almond MACAROONS were simply made with raw chopped almonds (like how I do it) and sweetened condensed milk (unlike mine)—not almond flour, though I know the flour is made from boiled and crushed almonds and isn't actually flour. 

Anyhow, I see what you're saying now.  :-)

